# Line-ending normalization.
#
# Commit LF, check out LF — on every platform. This repo is developed on
# macOS/Linux (always LF) but is distributed downstream, including to
# Windows-clean white-label forks. Without this file, line endings are left
# to each contributor's `core.autocrlf` setting and to whatever bytes a tool
# writes (e.g. Python text-mode writers emit CRLF on Windows), so files drift
# to CRLF the moment Windows enters the picture. `eol=lf` pins both the
# committed blob and the working tree to LF, eliminating that drift at the
# source regardless of platform or git config.
#
# After adding/changing this file, run `git add --renormalize .` once to
# rewrite any already-committed CRLF (a no-op in an all-LF tree).

* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files: never normalize.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.pdf  binary
*.zip  binary
*.gz   binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
